The paper proposes an end-to-end image clustering auto-encoder algorithm that uses various constraints to improve clustering performance. This work involves machine learning (ML) techniques, specifically deep learning, and computer vision (CV) techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper involves the use of data augmentation, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (AI) research. Hence, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a likely sub-category. The paper also uses the MMD distance, which is a statistical measure used in neural networks and optimization algorithms, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques, such as auto-encoder reconstruction loss constraint, which is a common technique in computational linguistics (CL), making cs.CL (Computation and Language) a possible sub-category.
